  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>\"What's the matter? Monkey got your tongue?\"</em> As a reaction when a hostile creature would damage you, you can in response make a small derogatory gesture and announce to the target that their attack will mean nothing. You cannot use this jutsu if you have 1 or more ranks of fear against the triggering creature.</p><p>Until the start of your next turn, you gain resistance to all damage and have advantage on saving throws from the triggering creature. However, your pronounced arrogance causes you to wain all concern. The triggering creature has advantage on attack rolls against you, and you cannot gain any bonuses to saving throws they impose on you outside of this jutsu and Elite Wukong features.</p><p><strong>At Higher Ranks:</strong> For each rank you cast this jutsu above D-Rank, increase the cost by 3, and reduce each instance of damage from the triggering creature by 1d8. If this jutsu is cast to A-Rank, you ignore effects that would prevent your saving throws from being made at advantage, and you halve the damage you receive from the creature, instead of gaining resistance (this cannot stack with resistance).</p>",
